How about using `skopeo copy` and `podman load`?
This image has the same digest.
(I don't know how to avoid to use skopeo)

```console
# x=quay.io/libpod/testimage:20221018
# bin/podman rmi -a
# bin/podman pull -q $x;bin/podman inspect $x > before
f5a99120db6452661930a1db3bf7390eec9b963f5f62c068fa32dc1d550afad3

# skopeo copy --all docker://$x dir:/tmp/testimage
Getting image list signatures
Copying 4 of 4 images in list
Copying image sha256:c7bce057af72480c1db9b2a4cc9d415eb46eb496a61e54d19517a13bf0877bb7 (1/4)

... snip ...

Storing list signatures
```

```console
# podman rmi -a
Untagged: quay.io/libpod/testimage:20221018
Deleted: f5a99120db6452661930a1db3bf7390eec9b963f5f62c068fa32dc1d550afad3
# podman load -q -i /tmp/testimage
Loaded image: sha256:f5a99120db6452661930a1db3bf7390eec9b963f5f62c068fa32dc1d550afad3
# podman tag f5a99120db64 $x
# podman inspect $x > after
```

